ZH: 他偷了我的钱包。
EN: He stole my wallet.

ZH: 我从商店里偷了一个苹果。
EN: I stole an apple from the store.

ZH: 她被发现偷了珠宝。
EN: She was caught stealing jewelry.

ZH: 这只小狗偷了我的拖鞋。
EN: This little dog stole my slipper.

ZH: 你不能偷别人的东西。
EN: You can't steal other people's things.

ZH: 他经常偷东西，所以已经被抓过好几次。
EN: He has been caught stealing several times because he steals things frequently.

ZH: 孩子们偷偷地做了一些糖果。
EN: The children secretly stole some candies.

ZH: 那个小偷已经多次偷窃在这个地区。
EN: The thief has stolen multiple times in this area.

ZH: 他偷我钢笔的行为让我非常生气。
EN: I was very angry when he stole my pen.

ZH: 别偷别人的快乐。
EN: Don't steal other people's happiness.

ZH: 她偷走了我的心。
EN: She stole my heart.

ZH: 他试图偷取公司的机密文件。
EN: He attempted to steal confidential documents from the company.

ZH: 小男孩总是偷他哥哥的玩具。
EN: The little boy always steals toys from his older brother.

ZH: 这家商店有人偷钱。
EN: Someone stole money from this shop.

ZH: 周末的演出被取消，因为有人偷了音响设备。
EN: The weekend performance was cancelled because someone stole the sound equipment.

ZH: 我小的时候常常偷吃零食。
EN: When I was young, I used to sneakily steal snacks.

ZH: 警察抓住了那名拿主意的小偷。
EN: The police caught the cunning thief.

ZH: 这只兔子偷吃了我的西红柿。
EN: The rabbit stole and ate my tomatoes.

ZH: 她坚持说那个小女孩偷走了她的笔记本。
EN: She insisted that the little girl stole her notebook.

ZH: 他为了喝醉酒而偷取了朋友的酒。
EN: He stole his friend's alcohol in order to get drunk.
